#### [Digital take-up](https://www.gov.uk/service-manual/measuring-success/measuring-digital-take-up)
* As Monitor my satellites is not replacing an existing service/non-digital channel and we have selected a user base at private beta, digital take up will be monitored by measuring:
  * The ratio of number of notifications sent to the number of log-ins and event information views per user (will be monitored through Notify and piwik pro). The correlation between these variables can also be monitored graphically over the course of private beta.
  * This metric will enable us to understand how often the operators use the service when there is an event that meets their thresholds and hence they are interested in.

## Additional KPIs specific to monitoring the success of MmS

During the private beta, key outputs to be assessed have been split into 3 categories; user satisfaction (already discussed above), service performance and user activity.

#### Service performance will be monitored by looking at:
* Mean time to repair, mean time between failures, mean time to acknowledge, mean time to fix
* Service availability (hours/day)
* Time for each page to load
* Time from API request to response
* Service downtime

#### User activity:
* Number of sign ins per user (Auth0)
* Number of notifications sent and delivered (monitored via Notify)
* Number of visits to different pages on the site and time spent there (piwik pro)
* Ephemeris uploads using the confirmation of successful ephemeris data as a proxy for this (piwik pro)
* Event Analysis uplaods using the confirmation of successful analysis data as a proxy for this (piwik pro)
* Where users come from (are they prompted by email notifications or sporadically visit the site to check in - referrels on piwik pro)

